main event: An observation of a bright light at Galena Airport, Alaska, on 20 Aug 60, which appeared white like a star and disappeared behind a cloud.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 30 seconds,The distance of the object was approximately 200 yards,The observation was correlated with a possible satellite sighting from Norne, Alaska,The object was described as the size of a pea,The radar indicated the object was on a NNE course.
witness description: Weather station personnel unable to get wide observations due to cloud cover.
